<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q11_v17" title="Q11_v17" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>Para calcular el volumen total de agua envasada en litros, se utiliza la siguiente regla:</p>
    <div>
      <m:math>
        <m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1,5</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi>
      </m:math>
    </div>
    <p>tal que b es el número de botellas llenas y V es el volumen total, medido en litros.</p>
    <p>Si 
      <m:math>
        <m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext> m³</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1000</m:mn><m:mtext> litros</m:mtext>
      </m:math>
      , ¿cuántos metros cúbicos de agua se envasan al llenar 
      <m:math>
        <m:mn>2800</m:mn>
      </m:math>
      botellas?
    </p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">0,42 metros cúbicos<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Con la regla dada, 1,5 × 2800 = 4 200 litros. Luego, como 1000 litros = 1 m³, se obtiene 4 200 ÷ 1000 = 4,2 m³. Por eso 0,42 m³ no corresponde al volumen pedido.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">4,2 metros cúbicos<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Aplicando la regla, 1,5 × 2800 = 4 200 litros. Después, 4 200 ÷ 1000 = 4,2 m³. Por lo tanto, al llenar 2800 botellas se envasan 4,2 metros cúbicos de agua.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">4200 metros cúbicos<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La regla entrega primero 4 200 litros, no 4 200 m³. Como 1000 litros = 1 m³, entonces 4 200 litros equivalen a 4,2 m³. Por eso 4200 m³ es un valor 1000 veces mayor que el correcto.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">2,8 metros cúbicos<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El problema no pide convertir 2800 botellas directamente a metros cúbicos. Primero se calcula el volumen en litros: 1,5 × 2800 = 4 200 litros. Luego, 4 200 ÷ 1000 = 4,2 m³. Por eso 2,8 m³ no satisface la regla dada.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Usar la regla del volumen en litros</strong></p>
            <p>La relación dada es:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1,5</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Como se llenan 2800 botellas, se reemplaza <strong>b</strong> por 2800:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1,5</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>2800</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Calcular el volumen total en litros</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>1,5</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>2800</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4200</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Entonces, el volumen total es <strong>4200 litros</strong>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Convertir litros a metros cúbicos</strong></p>
            <p>El enunciado indica que:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext> m³</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1000</m:mn><m:mtext> litros</m:mtext>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, para convertir 4200 litros a metros cúbicos, se divide por 1000:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>4200</m:mn><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>1000</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4,2</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>Al llenar 2800 botellas, se envasan <strong>4,2 metros cúbicos</strong> de agua.</p>
            <p>La alternativa correcta es <strong>B</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>